The Telegraph - Calcutta : Opinion
		 Monday, May 12, 2003 				 Systems that disperse the smoke
		 VENTILATION method: Firemen drill holes  on the roof of the underground market at Satyanarayan  Park to disperse the smokeSwapan Kumar Gupta: From the Satyanarayan Park AC Market blaze, we learnt that one can drill the roof of a structure to disperse smoke. Is there any other method that can be adopted to avoid drilling?																																																													In every big hotel or market, there is a smoke ventilating system. If there is heat or smoke, it automatically opens up. However, if there is a fire, the airconditioning machines should be shut down.
